parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a collision can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a collision
airbag warning light stays on
airbags deactivate without warning
no airbag deployment despite moderate to severe impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to false warnings, deactivation of the airbags, or failure to deploy in the event of a collision, compromising occupant safety.
symptoms: Airbag warning light stays on
airbags deactivate without warning
no airbag deployment despite moderate to severe impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the window defrost blower motor and rear window electric defrost to malfunction, leading to impaired visibility during winter or rain conditions, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The window defrost blower motor fails to work after starting the car
the rear window electric defrost fails
the ignition switch fails to return to the proper position
the driver must jiggle the key and ignition switch to restore power to the blower motor and rear defrost
the defrost blower motor stops working when hitting bumps in the road
smoke is seen coming from the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical components can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The battery fails
the tire system fails
the A/C system fails
other electrical components fail repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Incorrect Rear Wheel Bearing Assembly and Drum Installation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrect installation of the rear wheel bearing assembly and drum can cause the wheel to fall off while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel comes off while driving
the vehicle needs rear wheel bearing assembly replacement
the drum assembly is incompatible with the spindle
the braking components are affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Replacement Parts and Warehouse Management
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The provision of incorrect or outdated replacement parts can lead to continued safety risks, as well as frustration and financial burden for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Incorrect parts are sent for replacement
parts are incompatible with the vehicle
warehouse management errors lead to incorrect part shipment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked transfer case housing can cause oil leaks, which can lead to premature wear on the transfer case and other components, potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks
clear oily substance on the ground
transfer case noise or vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission stalling and failure can cause the vehicle to die in the middle of traffic, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls when shifting from park to drive or reverse
vehicle dies in the middle of traffic
vehicle stalls in the middle of an intersection
difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water entering the vehicle can cause electrical system failures, leading to safety risks, and create an unhealthy environment for occupants due to mildew growth.
symptoms: Water accumulation on the floor
mildew smell
electrical system malfunctions
and potential health issues for occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A bent frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, affecting its handling and stability, and increasing the risk of accidents. Stalling issues can cause sudden loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rough and bumpy ride
stalling when the air conditioning is on
potential loss of vehicle control.
